S1125.shortDescription: Boolean literals should not be redundant
S1125.fullDescription: Redundant Boolean literals should be removed from expressions to improve readability.

S1144.shortDescription: Unused private types or members should be removed
S1144.fullDescription: private or internal types or private members that are never executed or referenced are dead code: unnecessary, inoperative code that should be removed. Cleaning out dead code decreases the size of the maintained codebase, making it easier to understand the program and preventing bugs from being introduced.

S3251.shortDescription: Implementations should be provided for "partial" methods
S3251.fullDescription: partial methods allow an increased degree of flexibility in programming a system. Hooks can be added to generated code by invoking methods that define their signature, but might not have an implementation yet. But if the implementation is still missing when the code makes it to production, the compiler silently removes the call. In the best case scenario, such calls simply represent cruft, but in they worst case they are critical, missing functionality, the loss of which will lead to unexpected results at runtime.

S3903.shortDescription: Types should be defined in named namespaces
S3903.fullDescription: Types are declared in namespaces in order to prevent name collisions and as a way to organize them into the object hierarchy. Types that are defined outside any named namespace are in a global namespace that cannot be referenced in code.
